data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_10580777\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_10580777\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xfr1665702814868_2.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xfr1665702814868_2.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xfr1665702814868_2.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xfr1665702814868\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                     \n Define a New Translation Table \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Define your own device translation table if you want to modify how a device works, or address a device that is not yet supported.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__context_w2081ab1b5b1_w2082ab1b5_w2083ab1\">\n<div class=\"div prereq\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__topic_d63509e1_d63510e1_d63511e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__p_d63512e1_d63513e1_d63514e1\">Contact the device's distributor for a list of the control characters the device uses.</p>\n</div>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__topic_d63515e1_d63516e1_d63517e1\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__note_w2087ab1b5b1b3b1_w2088ab1b5b1b3_w2089ab1b5b1_w2090ab1b5_w2091ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Defining a complete table is difficult and should only be tackled by someone experienced in this area. If you need to define a translation table, it is much easier to duplicate and adapt an existing table than to create a new one from scratch. An existing definition can match your particular device quite closely, if not exactly.\n                       <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lrc1665702814941.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lrc1665702814941.html\" title=\"It is easier to adapt an existing table than to create a new one from scratch. An existing definition can match your particular device quite closely, if not exactly.\">Copy and Adapt an Existing Translation Table</a>.\n                    </div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__p_d63518e1_d63519e1_d63520e1\">For example, you may want to use national character sets or color preferences. If a device does not support a certain feature, such as graphic borderlines or color, the device can find a suitable approximation or leave the feature out.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__p_d63521e1_d63522e1_d63523e1\">To define a translation table:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__li_d27662e1_d27663e1_d27664e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span>, then choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Device\n                  Tables</span> or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Keyboard Tables</span>, according to the\n               type of translation table you are creating. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__li_d27665e1_d27666e1_d27667e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select or create the library to contain the table.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__note_w2092ab1b5b3b3b3b1_w2093ab1b5b3b3b3_w2094ab1b5b3b3_w2095ab1b5b3_w2096ab1b5_w2097ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Do not define the table in the USYS default library. It contains the standard definitions delivered with Uniface, and tables defined in this library may be overwritten when a new release of Uniface is installed.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__li_d27668e1_d27669e1_d27670e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__p_d63524e1_d63525e1_d63526e1\">Provide a name that corresponds to the output device or keyboard.\n For example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">VT200</code>for a VT200 terminal, or <code class=\"ph codeph\">FX80</code>for an FX80 printer.</span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__li_d27671e1_d27672e1_d27673e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__p_d63527e1_d63528e1_d63529e1\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Definition</span>, edit\n               the contents of the translation table using the appropriate syntax and mnemonics. For\n               more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tqs1665702815016.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tqs1665702815016.html\" title=\"A device translation table contains delimiters that mark the beginning and end of the table and sections within the table. Each section contains mapping definitions that define an output code sequence or character, the corresponding Uniface meta code (a function mnemonic or meta character), and optional description or comments.\">Device Translation Table Syntax</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ltj1703097709703.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ltj1703097709703.html\" title=\"Keyboard translation tables map input codes from keyboards or database to logical Uniface functions and characters.\">Keyboard Translation Table Syntax</a>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__li_d27674e1_d27675e1_d27676e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">File&gt;Compile</span></span> to compile the table.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__li_d27677e1_d27678e1_d27679e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Move the compiled definitions to a deployment archive using the Resources Manager.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__result_w2084ab1b5b5_w2085ab1b5_w2086ab1\">\n<div class=\"sectiondiv postreq\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__topic_d63530e1_d63531e1_d63532e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xfr1665702814868__p_d63533e1_d63534e1_d63535e1\">Once a table has been defined, you can import it into other Uniface installations.</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/btf1665702980888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Translation Tables</a><p>To mediate between itself and the external environment, Uniface uses translation tables. Translation tables provide input and output mappings between platform-specific device codes and Uniface functions, and between external and internal character sets. Uniface provides translation tables for the platforms it supports, but you can customize these or use them to create your own tables.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dzg1703255185600.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Guidelines for Defining Keyboard Translation Tables</a><p>When defining or adapting keyboard translation tables, there are some general guidelines you should follow.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_10580777\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_10580777\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define a New Translation Table Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define a New Translation Table Define your own device translation table if you want to modify how a device works, or address a device that is not yet supported. Contact the device's distributor for a list of the control characters the device uses. Note: Defining a complete table is difficult and should only be tackled by someone experienced in this area. If you need to define a translation table, it is much easier to duplicate and adapt an existing table than to create a new one from scratch. An existing definition can match your particular device quite closely, if not exactly. Copy and Adapt an Existing Translation Table . For example, you may want to use national character sets or color preferences. If a device does not support a certain feature, such as graphic borderlines or color, the device can find a suitable approximation or leave the feature out. To define a translation table: Click More Editors , then choose Device Tables or Keyboard Tables , according to the type of translation table you are creating. Select or create the library to contain the table. Note: Do not define the table in the USYS default library. It contains the standard definitions delivered with Uniface, and tables defined in this library may be overwritten when a new release of Uniface is installed. Provide a name that corresponds to the output device or keyboard. For example, VT200 for a VT200 terminal, or FX80 for an FX80 printer. In the Definition , edit the contents of the translation table using the appropriate syntax and mnemonics. For more information, see Device Translation Table Syntax and Keyboard Translation Table Syntax . Choose File>Compile to compile the table. Move the compiled definitions to a deployment archive using the Resources Manager. Once a table has been defined, you can import it into other Uniface installations. Related Links Translation Tables To mediate between itself and the external environment, Uniface uses translation tables. Translation tables provide input and output mappings between platform-specific device codes and Uniface functions, and between external and internal character sets. Uniface provides translation tables for the platforms it supports, but you can customize these or use them to create your own tables. Guidelines for Defining Keyboard Translation Tables When defining or adapting keyboard translation tables, there are some general guidelines you should follow. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}